 in particle injection prevented the efficiency of particle acceleration\nand magnetic field amplification from increasing. We argue, however, that more\nadvanced (possibly, non-resonant) models of turbulence generation and\ndissipation may lead to a scenario in which particle injection boost due to\nturbulence dissipation results in more efficient acceleration and even stronger\namplified magnetic fields than without the dissipation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Jul 2008 19:59:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 Jul 2008 15:18:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 30 Jul 2008 20:48:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
