ific heat. The specific heat coefficient exponent we obtain (0.39) is in\nexcellent agreement with the experimental result at low temperatures (0.4).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Jul 2008 20:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 13 Jul 2008 16:15:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
